node.text: Very important to know. I see people all the time on their phones and never glancing up and looking around. Scary.

So often we become so comfortable in our own hometowns that we forget to stay alert. This is apparent with outdoor sport enthusiasts quite often. Headphones, playing with your phone...it’s easy to become complacent and unaware of your surroundings. Remember even the “safest” areas can make you a victim. Always be prepared no matter where you are. **I did not mention paying attention to time of day/lack of lighting and that in this particular area, the best place to retreat is the closest house in the neighborhood IF POSSIBLE. 
#wethefemale #strongwomensafecommunities #notavictim #metoo #situationalawareness #personalsecurity #empoweringwomen 
#selfdefense

@charlie_bales I do.... but that is not why I conceal carry. I conceal carry to use as an absolute last resort. I would much rather not put myself in a position to need to use my firearm if I can. That’s the point of this video. If you’re one of those people that carries to just look for reason to use your firearm, then you’re part of our problem

@wethefemale_official the video didn’t talk about conceal carrying, it talked about situational awareness both are key. Situational awareness to prevent if possible and conceal carry to defend if needed.

@womensfirearmassociation This is me in the video. I always carry. However not every woman is comfortable with carrying a firearm. That is okay. 
Our mission is to educate woman with options to keep them safe. 
Most scenarios in which a firearm would be used could be avoided with proper situational awareness. 
While we support a woman’s right to choose whatever method of self defense she is comfortable with, it is not our place to make the decision regarding what’s best for her. 
This video, along with subsequent videos will be focused on how to not need a weapon to begin with.
